replies.bodyText:
This may result in the appearance of a resource leak when the partition count is large, hits on partitions are sparse and shifting. Example: 1,000 partitions. Partition 1 is hot for a short period of time causing numerous connections to be opened. Now partition 2 is hot. Then partition 3,... Half the partitions then go dormant. These connections might last 24 hours without being used.
Alternatively, in another PR, we might consider changing the algorithm so one connection stays open. We’d consume fewer resources unnecessarily. I’d like some time to think about the specifics of how this might work.
@moderakh let’s chat about this offline.

